Constructor Detail

DefaultSmallStepProofRule

DefaultSmallStepProofRule(int group,
                          String name,
                          boolean axiom)
Allocates a new DefaultSmallStepProofRule with the specified name. If axiom is true, the new rule has no premises, otherwise it has exactly one premise.

Parameters:
group - the group id of the small step rule, see the description of the AbstractProofRule.getGroup() method for details.
name - the name of the rule.
axiom - true if the rule has no premises.
Throws:
NullPointerException - if name is null.
See Also:
isAxiom()
Method Detail

isAxiom

public boolean isAxiom()
Returns true if this rule is an axiom, which does not have any premises. Otherwise, if the rule has exactly one premises (small step rules cannot have more than one premise), false is returned (this is called a meta rule then).

Specified by:
isAxiom in interface SmallStepProofRule
Returns:
true if the proof rule has no premises.
See Also:
SmallStepProofRule.isAxiom()

toExnRule

public SmallStepProofRule toExnRule()
Returns the EXN rule for this meta rule. If this rule is an axiom or an EXN in itself, this method will return a reference to this rule instead (this does not really make sense, but it is convenient to use).

Specified by:
toExnRule in interface SmallStepProofRule
Returns:
the EXN rule for this meta rule.

SmallStepProofRule.toExnRule()
